HANTAVIRUS - AMERICAS (04): CHILE (LOS LAGOS, NUBLE)
****************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

In this update:
[1] Los Lagos
[2] Nuble

******
[1] Los Lagos
Date: Tue 18 Jan 2022
Source: Biobio Chile [in Spanish, trans., edited]
https://www.biobiochile.cl/noticias/nacional/region-de-los-lagos/2022/01/18/muere-hombre-con-sospecha-de-contagio-de-virus-hanta-en-maullin.shtml


This Sunday [16 Jan 2022] the death of a man was registered who was suspected [to have an infection] with a hantavirus. Health authorities began an epidemiological investigation in the Astillero sector to determine where the infection was acquired.

A health authority confirmed the death of a man who was suspected of a hantavirus [infection] in Majllin in the Los Lagos region. The patient was hospitalized in the Tamuco hospital.

According to the information [provided], on Friday [15 Jan 2022] a rapid test was done that was positive for a hantavirus. He then was moved to the Araucania region where he died on Sunday morning [16 Jan 2022].

The dead individual was about 40 years old and was a resident of the Astillero costal area. Due to this, an environmental epidemiological investigation is carried out in this area to establish the site of contagion.

The Los Lagos SEREMI [Secretaria Regional Ministerial de Salud; regional health ministerial secretariat], Marcela Cardenas, stated that among the possible places is an outbuilding near the man's residence that was used as a storage shed. The shed was used to store hay and forage and apparently had not been ventilated.

Following the case, educational and cleaning work is being reinforced in sectors that receive visitors during the summer.

[byline: Daniela Salgado]

